articles.title: Box Office: ‘IF’ Stumbles on Opening Day With $10.3 Million, ‘The Strangers: Chapter 1’ Unmasking Third Place - Variety
articles.description: Ryan Reynolds and John Krasinski's imaginary friends comedy "IF" will open atop domestic charts, while "The Strangers: Chapter 1" also debuts.
articles.content: Paramount’s family comedy “IF” is leading domestic charts in its opening after earning $10.3 million from 4,041 locations across Friday and preview screenings. But the John Krasinski-directed fantasy… [+3377 chars]
